15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 1356, as
17 last amended by Section 1, Chapter 392, O.S.L. 2025 (68 O.S. Supp.
18 2025, Section 1356), is amended to read as follows:
19 Section 1356. Exemptions - Governmental and nonprofit entities.
20 There are hereby specifically exempted from the tax levied by
21 Section 1350 et seq. of this title:
22 1. Sale of tangible personal property or services to the United
23 States government or to this state, any political subdivision of
24 this state, or any agency of a political subdivision of this state
Req. No. 16429 Page 1

1 or a public trust, organized pursuant to the provisions of Section
2 176 et seq. of Title 60 of the Oklahoma Statutes, with a
3 municipality as the beneficiary of such trust; provided, all sales
4 to contractors in connection with the performance of any contract
5 with the United States government, this state, or any of its
6 political subdivisions shall not be exempted from the tax levied by
7 Section 1350 et seq. of this title, except as hereinafter provided;
8 2. Sales of property to agents appointed by or under contract
9 with agencies or instrumentalities of the United States government
