Req. No. 16429 Page 21

1 1353 of this title and the vendor shall be required to collect the
2 sales tax otherwise applicable to the transaction. The purchaser
3 may apply for a refund of the sales tax paid in the manner
4 prescribed by this paragraph. Within thirty (30) days after the end
5 of each fiscal year, any purchaser that is entitled to make
6 application for a refund based upon the exempt treatment authorized
7 by this paragraph may file an application for refund of the sales
8 taxes paid during such preceding fiscal year. The Oklahoma Tax
9 Commission shall prescribe a form for purposes of making the
10 application for refund. The Tax Commission shall determine whether
11 or not the total amount of sales tax exemptions claimed by all
12 purchasers is equal to or less than Six Hundred Fifty Thousand
13 Dollars ($650,000.00). If such claims are less than or equal to
14 that amount, the Tax Commission shall make refunds to the purchasers
15 in the full amount of the documented and verified sales tax amounts.
16 If such claims by all purchasers are in excess of Six Hundred Fifty
17 Thousand Dollars ($650,000.00), the Tax Commission shall determine
18 the amount of each purchaser's claim, the total amount of all claims
19 by all purchasers, and the percentage each purchaser's claim amount
20 bears to the total. The resulting percentage determined for each
21 purchaser shall be multiplied by Six Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars
22 ($650,000.00) to determine the amount of refundable sales tax to be
23 paid to each purchaser. The pro rata refund amount shall be the
24 only method to recover sales taxes paid during the preceding fiscal
Req. No. 16429 Page 22

1 year and no balance of any sales taxes paid on a pro rata basis
2 shall be the subject of any subsequent refund claim pursuant to this
3 paragraph;
